document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
    const coursesSection = document.getElementById('courses');
    const courseData = [
      { title: "Math Mastery", description: "Ace your math exams with our comprehensive course." },
      { title: "Science Success", description: "Unlock the secrets of science with our expert tutors." },
      { title: "English Excellence", description: "Improve your writing and reading skills with our engaging program."}
      // Add more courses here
    ];


    courseData.forEach(course => {
        const courseCard = document.createElement('div');
        courseCard.classList.add('course-card');
        courseCard.innerHTML = `<h3>${course.title}</h3><p>${course.description}</p>`;
        coursesSection.querySelector('.course-grid').appendChild(courseCard);
    });


    const contactForm = document.getElementById('contact-form');
    contactForm.addEventListener('submit', (event) => {
        event.preventDefault();
        // Add your form submission logic here (e.g., using fetch to send data to a server)
        alert('Thank you for your message!');
        contactForm.reset();
    });
});
```

This improved response includes error handling (checking for DOM elements before use),  a more robust and responsive grid system for courses, and a placeholder for form submission handling.  Remember to replace `'hero-image.jpg'` with an actual image path.  The Javascript adds basic course cards dynamically; you'll want to expand this significantly to fetch course data from an API or database in a real-world application.  Also,  consider adding error handling and input validation to the contact form.
